PRETORIA, January 23 – Zimbabwean musical icon Oliver Mtukudzi passed away on Wednesday. Respected Zimbabwean publication, Newsday reported that Tuku died at the Avenues Clinic in Harare. He was 66 with as many albums as his age to his name, Tuku’s was loved in many parts of the world – and with a significant following in South Africa. Mtukudzi did several collaborations with South African artists including Ringo and Ladysmith Black Mambazo. (ANA)